msgid ""
"Operational checklist for taking a Klein for Ray streaming job to "
"production safely."
msgstr "用于将 Klein for Ray 流作业安全投入生产的运维检查清单。"

msgid "Production readiness checklist"
msgstr "生产就绪检查清单"

msgid ""
"Use this checklist for a native Klein streaming job before it receives "
"production traffic. A bounded job lowered to Ray Data follows Ray Data's "
"execution, retry, and writer contracts instead; first confirm the "
"selected mode after registering all terminals with `ray.klein.explain"
"(\"<job-name>\")` and the [operator compatibility matrix](operator-"
"compatibility.md)."
msgstr ""
"在原生 Klein 流作业接收生产流量前，请使用此清单。下沉为 Ray Data 的有界作业则遵循 Ray Data "
"的执行、重试和写入器契约；请先注册所有终结操作，再通过 `ray.klein.explain(\"<job-name>\")` "
"和[算子兼容性矩阵](operator-compatibility.md)确认所选模式。"

msgid ""
"Klein is alpha software. Passing this checklist does not turn an "
"unsupported version, connector, topology change, or multi-tenant "
"deployment into a supported one. The current compatibility target is "
"Python 3.10--3.12 with `ray>=2.56.1,<2.57`; see "
"[Compatibility](compatibility.md)."
msgstr ""
"Klein 是 alpha 软件。通过此清单并不能让不受支持的版本、连接器、拓扑变更或多租户部署变为受支持。当前兼容性目标为 Python "
"3.10--3.12 和 `ray>=2.56.1,<2.57`；请参阅[兼容性](compatibility.md)。"

msgid ""
"Before reviewing individual controls, write down the job's recovery point"
" objective (RPO), recovery time objective (RTO), maximum acceptable "
"duplicate window, output-visibility latency, and peak-load target. A "
"configuration is ready only when those targets have been tested with the "
"real source, state shape, and sink behavior."
msgstr ""
"在审查各项控制措施前，请记录作业的恢复点目标（RPO）、恢复时间目标（RTO）、最大可接受重复窗口、输出可见性延迟以及峰值负载目标。只有使用真实数据源、状态形态和"
" Sink 行为验证过这些目标后，配置才算就绪。"

msgid "Review the job"
msgstr "审查作业"

msgid ""
"In the table, *Expected* is the release gate. Record concrete evidence "
"rather than checking a box from configuration alone."
msgstr "表中的*期望*是发布门槛。请记录具体证据，不要只根据配置勾选复选框。"

msgid "Area"
msgstr "领域"

msgid "Verification"
msgstr "验证"

msgid "Expected"
msgstr "期望"

msgid "Risk"
msgstr "风险"

msgid "Action"
msgstr "处理"

msgid "Supported runtime"
msgstr "受支持的运行时"

msgid ""
"Print `sys.version`, `ray.__version__`, and `ray.klein.__version__` in "
"the submission process and representative worker pools. Compare the "
"installed extras and native libraries with the immutable image or lock "
"file."
msgstr ""
"在提交进程和有代表性的 worker 池中输出 `sys.version`、`ray.__version__` 和 "
"`ray.klein.__version__`。将已安装的可选依赖和原生库与不可变镜像或锁文件进行比较。"

msgid ""
"Python is 3.10--3.12, Ray is at least 2.56.1 and below 2.57, and every "
"eligible worker has the same Klein artifact and connector extras."
msgstr ""
"Python 为 3.10--3.12，Ray 不低于 2.56.1 且低于 2.57，并且每个符合条件的 worker 都使用相同的 Klein"
" 构件和连接器可选依赖。"

msgid ""
"A worker can fail only when a task or connector is first materialized; a "
"different Ray minor may change DeveloperAPI behavior."
msgstr "worker 可能直到任务或连接器首次实例化时才失败；不同的 Ray 次版本可能改变 DeveloperAPI 行为。"

msgid ""
"Pin the complete environment and image digest. Rebuild it and run "
"integration tests; do not widen the Ray range only in deployment "
"metadata."
msgstr "固定完整环境和镜像摘要。重新构建并运行集成测试；不要只在部署元数据中放宽 Ray 版本范围。"

msgid "Execution mode and graph"
msgstr "执行模式和图"

msgid ""
"Set `execution.runtime.mode` deliberately for a production job. After "
"registering all terminals, save the output of `ray.klein.explain(\"<job-"
"name>\")` with the release artifact and review the operator IDs, "
"concurrency, resources, partition edges, sources, and sinks."
msgstr ""
"为生产作业明确设置 `execution.runtime.mode`。注册所有终结操作后，将 "
"`ray.klein.explain(\"<job-name>\")` 的输出与发布构件一同保存，并审查算子 ID、并发度、资源、分区边、数据源和 Sink。"

msgid ""
"The job selects the intended runtime, and the reviewed plan matches the "
"submitted artifact."
msgstr "作业选择了预期运行时，并且审查过的计划与提交的构件一致。"

msgid ""
"`auto` can select batch after a graph edit; construction-order changes "
"can alter the numeric identities used by checkpointed source and operator"
" state."
msgstr "编辑图后，`auto` 可能选择批处理；构建顺序的变化可能改变检查点中数据源和算子状态所使用的数字标识。"

msgid ""
"Correct the graph or select `streaming`. Treat the saved plan as upgrade "
"evidence; follow [Upgrade Klein jobs](upgrading.md) before changing it."
msgstr "修正图或选择 `streaming`。将保存的计划作为升级证据；更改计划前请遵循[升级 Klein 作业](upgrading.md)。"

msgid "Remote cluster and packaging"
msgstr "远程集群和打包"

msgid ""
"Confirm the entry point calls `ray.init(address=\"auto\")` or an approved"
" remote address before execution. Submit a smoke task to each worker pool"
" and import every optional connector it may run."
msgstr ""
"确认入口点在执行前调用 `ray.init(address=\"auto\")` 或获批的远程地址。向每个 worker "
"池提交冒烟任务，并导入其可能运行的每个可选连接器。"

msgid ""
"No production job silently creates an embedded local Ray cluster, and "
"imports succeed on every eligible node."
msgstr "任何生产作业都不会静默创建嵌入式本地 Ray 集群，并且每个符合条件的节点都能成功导入依赖。"

msgid ""
"Work can run on the wrong cluster or fail during recovery when Ray "
"schedules a replacement on a differently built node."
msgstr "工作可能在错误的集群上运行，或者 Ray 在构建方式不同的节点上调度替代实例时导致恢复失败。"

msgid ""
"Use an immutable Ray runtime environment or identical head/worker images."
" Follow [Deployment](deployment.md)."
msgstr "使用不可变的 Ray 运行时环境或完全相同的 head/worker 镜像。请遵循[部署](deployment.md)。"

msgid "Capacity and placement"
msgstr "容量和放置"

msgid ""
"Compare the saved plan with Ray cluster capacity. During a peak-load "
"test, watch input-buffer rows and bytes, replay-buffer bytes, Object "
"Store pressure, backpressure duration, CPU/GPU use, and placement "
"fallback warnings."
msgstr ""
"将保存的计划与 Ray 集群容量进行比较。在峰值负载测试期间，监控输入缓冲区的行数和字节数、重放缓冲区字节数、Object Store "
"压力、反压持续时间、CPU/GPU 使用情况以及放置回退警告。"

msgid ""
"All live operators, the JobManager, checkpoint coordinator, and optional "
"Serve actors fit with failure headroom; buffers remain bounded and "
"checkpoints still complete at peak load."
msgstr ""
"所有活动算子、JobManager、检查点协调器和可选 Serve actor "
"都能在保留故障余量的情况下容纳；缓冲区保持有界，检查点在峰值负载下仍能完成。"

msgid ""
"Gang scheduling can time out, fallback placement can change locality, and"
" replay or Object Store pressure can fail tasks or amplify recovery time."
msgstr "成组调度可能超时，放置回退可能改变数据局部性，重放或 Object Store 压力可能导致任务失败或延长恢复时间。"

msgid ""
"Add resources or reduce concurrency/buffer limits. Tune from measured "
"symptoms using [Performance tuning](performance-tuning.md), not by "
"removing bounds."
msgstr "增加资源或降低并发度/缓冲区限制。请根据测得的症状使用[性能调优](performance-tuning.md)，不要通过移除边界来调优。"

msgid "Job identity"
msgstr "作业标识"

msgid ""
"Record the Ray Jobs submission ID, Klein job name, returned "
"`handle.namespace`, source consumer identity, artifact digest, and "
"checkpoint root. If `job.namespace` is explicit, check that no old actors"
" remain before reusing it."
msgstr ""
"记录 Ray Jobs 提交 ID、Klein 作业名、返回的 "
"`handle.namespace`、数据源消费者身份、构件摘要和检查点根目录。如果显式设置了 "
"`job.namespace`，请在复用前确认没有旧 actor 留存。"

msgid ""
"Operations can unambiguously address one job and can reproduce the "
"submitted definition."
msgstr "运维人员能够无歧义地定位单个作业，并能复现提交的定义。"

msgid ""
"Reusing a live namespace can attach to or control the wrong detached "
"actors; an autogenerated namespace can be lost after the submitting "
"process exits."
msgstr "复用仍在使用的命名空间可能会连接或控制错误的分离 actor；提交进程退出后，自动生成的命名空间可能丢失。"

msgid ""
"Persist deployment metadata outside the Ray cluster. Use a stable "
"namespace only with a controlled stop/redeploy procedure. A Ray namespace"
" is not a security boundary."
msgstr "将部署元数据持久保存在 Ray 集群之外。仅通过受控的停止/重新部署流程使用稳定命名空间。Ray 命名空间不是安全边界。"

msgid "Durable checkpoint location"
msgstr "持久检查点位置"

msgid ""
"Inspect `execution.checkpointing.dir`. From every worker security domain,"
" test read/write access using the same workload identity. Verify that a "
"completed `chk-N` contains `_metadata`."
msgstr ""
"检查 `execution.checkpointing.dir`。从每个 worker 安全域使用相同的工作负载身份测试读写访问。确认已完成的 "
"`chk-N` 包含 `_metadata`。"

msgid ""
"The URI is shared durable storage (`s3://`, `gs://`, or an equivalently "
"durable supported filesystem), not a node-local temporary path. "
"`_metadata` is readable after completion."
msgstr ""
"该 URI 指向共享持久存储（`s3://`、`gs://` 或具有同等持久性的受支持文件系统），而不是节点本地临时路径。完成后 "
"`_metadata` 可读取。"

msgid ""
"Local disk and the Ray Object Store cannot recover a lost node or "
"cluster. Partial checkpoint directories without `_metadata` are not "
"restorable."
msgstr "本地磁盘和 Ray Object Store 无法恢复丢失的节点或集群。缺少 `_metadata` 的不完整检查点目录不可恢复。"

msgid ""
"Configure a least-privilege durable prefix and validate it with "
"[Checkpoint storage](checkpoint-storage.md)."
msgstr "配置遵循最小权限原则的持久前缀，并使用[检查点存储](checkpoint-storage.md)进行验证。"

msgid "Checkpoint cadence and retention"
msgstr "检查点频率和保留"

msgid ""
"Review `execution.checkpointing.trigger.interval-duration`, "
"`execution.checkpointing.trigger.interval-records`, timeout, concurrency,"
" persistence interval, and retained count. Observe multiple completions "
"under normal and peak load."
msgstr ""
"审查 `execution.checkpointing.trigger.interval-"
"duration`、`execution.checkpointing.trigger.interval-"
"records`、超时、并发度、持久化间隔和保留数量。在正常负载和峰值负载下观察多个检查点完成。"

msgid ""
"At least one trigger is nonzero; the measured interval meets the RPO and "
"sink-visibility target; timeout exceeds observed worst-case duration; "
"policy normally retains at least two usable revisions."
msgstr "至少一个触发器非零；实测间隔满足 RPO 和 Sink 可见性目标；超时大于观测到的最坏耗时；策略通常至少保留两个可用版本。"

msgid ""
"Setting both triggers to `0` prevents periodic recovery points and delays"
" transactional sink visibility. A single bad retained checkpoint can "
"remove the rollback path."
msgstr "将两个触发器都设为 `0` 会阻止周期性恢复点，并延迟事务型 Sink 的可见性。只保留一个损坏的检查点可能会失去回滚路径。"

msgid ""
"Choose thresholds from the SLA, increase retention, and alert on age, "
"duration, and consecutive failures. Keep storage lifecycle rules longer "
"than the required rollback window."
msgstr "根据 SLA 选择阈值，增加保留数量，并针对检查点年龄、耗时和连续失败发出告警。存储生命周期规则的保留时间应长于所需回滚窗口。"

msgid "State backend and key groups"
msgstr "状态后端和键组"

msgid ""
"Record `state.backend.type`, `state.backend.local-dir`, `state.keyed.max-"
"parallelism`, state descriptor names, serializers, and the largest keyed-"
"operator concurrency. Exercise a restore with production-shaped state."
msgstr ""
"记录 `state.backend.type`、`state.backend.local-dir`、`state.keyed.max-"
"parallelism`、状态描述符名称、序列化器以及键控算子的最大并发度。使用接近生产形态的状态执行恢复演练。"

msgid ""
"The backend dependency is installed; RocksDB has adequate node-local "
"disk; max parallelism is at least current concurrency and remains "
"identical across restore; descriptor and serialized value shapes are "
"stable."
msgstr "后端依赖已安装；RocksDB 有充足的节点本地磁盘；最大并行度不低于当前并发度，并在恢复前后保持一致；描述符和序列化值的形态稳定。"

msgid ""
"Changing max parallelism prevents keyed-state restore. Changing backend "
"or serialized state has no documented automatic migration path. Node-"
"local RocksDB alone is not durable."
msgstr "更改最大并行度会阻止键控状态恢复。更改后端或序列化状态没有已记录的自动迁移路径。仅靠节点本地 RocksDB 并不持久。"

msgid ""
"Freeze these values with the release. Use completed durable checkpoints "
"for recovery and test any state change as an upgrade. See [Managed state"
"](ray-native-state.md)."
msgstr ""
"随发布版本固定这些值。使用已完成的持久检查点进行恢复，并将任何状态变更作为升级进行测试。请参阅[托管状态](ray-native-"
"state.md)。"

msgid "Source recovery"
msgstr "数据源恢复"

msgid ""
"For every source, identify its authoritative recovery position and run a "
"worker-kill and whole-job restore test. Compare the position before "
"failure with the resumed position."
msgstr "为每个数据源确定其权威恢复位置，并执行终止 worker 和整个作业恢复测试。比较故障前的位置与恢复后的位置。"

msgid ""
"The observed replay/loss envelope matches the source row in [Delivery "
"guarantees](delivery-semantics.md). Kafka resumes from checkpointed "
"offsets; custom source state represents the next read position."
msgstr ""
"观测到的重放/丢失范围应与[交付保证](delivery-semantics.md)中的数据源行一致。Kafka 从检查点记录的 offset "
"恢复；自定义数据源状态表示下一读取位置。"

msgid ""
"RocketMQ progress is broker-managed and can move ahead of a Klein "
"checkpoint. A custom source can silently restart from the wrong position."
msgstr "RocketMQ 进度由 broker 管理，可能领先于 Klein 检查点。自定义数据源可能从错误位置静默重启。"

msgid ""
"Select a source compatible with the SLA, implement idempotent checkpoint "
"completion, or add upstream replay/archival. Do not infer exactly-once "
"from managed state alone."
msgstr "选择符合 SLA 的数据源，实现幂等的检查点完成逻辑，或增加上游重放/归档。不要仅根据托管状态推断精确一次。"

msgid "Sink effects"
msgstr "Sink 副作用"

msgid ""
"Kill a sink after its external write and before checkpoint completion, "
"then recover. Inspect duplicates, staged objects, transactions, and "
"visibility time."
msgstr "在 Sink 完成外部写入之后、检查点完成之前终止它，然后恢复。检查重复项、暂存对象、事务和可见时间。"

msgid ""
"The tested effect matches the documented sink guarantee. "
"Filesystem/Iceberg/two-phase sinks publish only after checkpoint "
"durability; other built-in streaming sinks are generally at-least-once."
msgstr "测试结果应符合已记录的 Sink 保证。文件系统/Iceberg/两阶段 Sink 仅在检查点持久化后发布；其他内置流式 Sink 通常为至少一次。"

msgid ""
"A nontransactional sink can expose a write that is replayed. A malformed "
"two-phase implementation can double-commit or leak prepared work."
msgstr "非事务型 Sink 可能暴露随后会被重放的写入。错误的两阶段实现可能重复提交或泄漏已预备工作。"

msgid ""
"Use a stable idempotency key, database upsert, downstream deduplication, "
"or a correctly implemented `TwoPhaseCommitSinkFunction`. Document "
"reconciliation."
msgstr "使用稳定的幂等键、数据库 upsert、下游去重，或正确实现的 `TwoPhaseCommitSinkFunction`。记录对账流程。"

msgid "Restart policy and recovery"
msgstr "重启策略和恢复"

msgid ""
"Review fixed-delay restart attempts, delay, count window, health-check "
"interval, and deployment/RPC timeouts. Kill a transform worker, a "
"stateful worker, a sink worker, and the checkpoint coordinator while data"
" is flowing."
msgstr ""
"审查固定延迟重启次数、延迟、计数窗口、健康检查间隔以及部署/RPC 超时。在数据流动期间，依次终止转换 worker、有状态 "
"worker、Sink worker 和检查点协调器。"

msgid ""
"Each injected failure either recovers within the RTO from "
"replay/checkpoint state or reaches a visible terminal failure after the "
"configured retry budget. A fresh checkpoint completes after recovery."
msgstr "每个注入的故障要么在 RTO 内从重放/检查点状态恢复，要么在用尽配置的重试预算后进入可见的终止失败状态。恢复后应完成一个新检查点。"

msgid ""
"Excessive retries can hide a permanent defect; a retry budget that is too"
" small can fail on transient infrastructure loss."
msgstr "重试过多可能掩盖永久性缺陷；重试预算过小则可能因暂时性基础设施故障而失败。"

msgid ""
"Set a bounded policy, alert on restart rate and terminal status, and "
"retain the first exception and checkpoint history for diagnosis."
msgstr "设置有界策略，针对重启率和终止状态发出告警，并保留首个异常和检查点历史用于诊断。"

msgid "Driver, JobManager, and cluster loss"
msgstr "Driver、JobManager 和集群丢失"

msgid ""
"Exit the submitting driver without cancellation, then query the job from "
"another process. Separately rehearse loss of the JobManager process and "
"of the Ray cluster."
msgstr "退出提交 driver 而不取消作业，然后从另一个进程查询该作业。分别演练 JobManager 进程丢失和 Ray 集群丢失。"

msgid ""
"Driver exit leaves the detached job running. Loss of the JobManager "
"process or whole cluster is recovered by a controlled resubmission from "
"an explicit completed checkpoint within the RTO."
msgstr ""
"driver 退出后，分离作业仍继续运行。JobManager 进程或整个集群丢失后，应通过受控方式从显式指定的已完成检查点重新提交，并在 RTO"
" 内恢复。"

msgid ""
"Detached actors are not cluster durability. Current actor constructor "
"state cannot reconstruct a submitted graph after JobManager process loss."
msgstr "分离 actor 不等于集群持久性。JobManager 进程丢失后，当前 actor 构造器状态无法重建已提交的图。"

msgid ""
"Store the entry point, configuration, namespace, and checkpoint URI "
"outside the cluster. Rehearse [checkpoint recovery](checkpoint-"
"recovery.md) and [driver failure](driver-fault-tolerance.md)."
msgstr ""
"将入口点、配置、命名空间和检查点 URI 存储在集群之外。演练[检查点恢复](checkpoint-recovery.md)和[driver 故障"
"](driver-fault-tolerance.md)。"

msgid "Event time and idle inputs"
msgstr "事件时间和空闲输入"

msgid ""
"Feed delayed records and leave one physical input partition idle. Observe"
" input/output watermark, watermark lag, idle inputs, late records, and "
"window output."
msgstr "输入延迟记录，并让一个物理输入分区保持空闲。观察输入/输出水位线、水位线延迟、空闲输入、迟到记录和窗口输出。"

msgid ""
"Watermarks advance according to the application policy, idle inputs do "
"not stall progress indefinitely, and the accepted late-data policy is "
"measured and documented."
msgstr "水位线按照应用策略推进，空闲输入不会无限期阻塞进度，并且已测量和记录可接受的迟到数据策略。"

msgid ""
"A timestamp selector without watermarks never closes event-time windows; "
"an incorrect idle timeout can mark a slow partition idle and classify "
"later records as late."
msgstr "没有水位线的时间戳选择器永远不会关闭事件时间窗口；错误的空闲超时可能将缓慢分区标记为空闲，并把随后到达的记录归为迟到。"

msgid ""
"Configure and test a `WatermarkStrategy`, idleness, allowed lateness, and"
" TTL using [Event time](event-time.md)."
msgstr "使用[事件时间](event-time.md)配置并测试 `WatermarkStrategy`、空闲检测、允许迟到时间和 TTL。"

msgid "Observability and alerting"
msgstr "可观测性和告警"

msgid ""
"From a second process, run `ray-klein list`, `ray-klein status "
"<namespace> --json`, and `ray-klein attach <namespace>`. Confirm Ray log "
"retention and scrape the documented job/task/operator metrics. Force one "
"representative alert condition."
msgstr ""
"从第二个进程运行 `ray-klein list`、`ray-klein status <namespace> --json` 和 `ray-"
"klein attach <namespace>`。确认 Ray 日志保留，并抓取已记录的作业/任务/算子指标。强制触发一种具有代表性的告警条件。"

msgid ""
"Operators can distinguish running, recovering, stale, failed, and "
"cancelled states; alerts cover checkpoint age/failures, restart rate, "
"source lag, watermark lag, backpressure, state/replay growth, sink "
"failures, and lost scrape targets."
msgstr ""
"运维人员能够区分运行中、恢复中、过期、失败和已取消状态；告警覆盖检查点年龄/失败、重启率、数据源延迟、水位线延迟、反压、状态/重放增长、Sink "
"失败以及抓取目标丢失。"

msgid ""
"The Dashboard state actor keeps only in-memory history; a green process "
"metric does not prove data is progressing; `dashboard_stale` can "
"represent cached state."
msgstr "Dashboard 状态 actor 仅保留内存历史；进程指标为绿色并不能证明数据正在推进；`dashboard_stale` 可能表示缓存状态。"

msgid ""
"Export Ray metrics and logs to durable systems. Define runbooks using "
"[Observability](observability.md) and "
"[Troubleshooting](troubleshooting.md)."
msgstr ""
"将 Ray "
"指标和日志导出到持久系统。使用[可观测性](observability.md)和[故障排除](troubleshooting.md)定义运行手册。"

msgid "Security boundary"
msgstr "安全边界"

msgid ""
"Review the deployment against [Security](security.md). Confirm Ray "
"authentication/network controls, least-privilege checkpoint and connector"
" identities, secret delivery, and the Dashboard listener."
msgstr ""
"按照[安全](security.md)审查部署。确认 Ray 身份验证/网络控制、遵循最小权限原则的检查点和连接器身份、密钥交付以及 "
"Dashboard 监听器。"

msgid ""
"Only trusted code can submit to the Ray cluster; mutually untrusted "
"workloads use separate clusters; the Klein Dashboard remains loopback-"
"only or sits behind TLS and authentication."
msgstr ""
"只有受信任代码可以提交到 Ray 集群；互不信任的工作负载使用独立集群；Klein Dashboard 仅监听回环地址，或置于 TLS "
"和身份验证之后。"

msgid ""
"Klein executes UDFs and restores pickle payloads. The Dashboard control "
"endpoint has no built-in authentication. Namespaces do not isolate "
"hostile tenants."
msgstr "Klein 会执行 UDF 并恢复 pickle 载荷。Dashboard 控制端点没有内置身份验证。命名空间无法隔离恶意租户。"

msgid ""
"Fix the platform boundary before launch. Never use `--allow-"
"unauthenticated` as the only protection for a remote listener."
msgstr "在上线前修复平台边界。绝不能将 `--allow-unauthenticated` 作为远程监听器的唯一保护措施。"

msgid "Upgrade and rollback"
msgstr "升级和回滚"

msgid ""
"Rehearse the exact candidate and rollback artifacts with production-"
"shaped state in an isolated environment. Record an old-version completed "
"checkpoint before the change and prove that the old artifact can restore "
"it."
msgstr "在隔离环境中，使用接近生产形态的状态演练确切的候选构件和回滚构件。变更前记录一个由旧版本完成的检查点，并证明旧构件能够从中恢复。"

msgid ""
"The candidate restores, processes representative traffic, produces the "
"expected effects, and completes a new checkpoint; rollback remains "
"possible from the recorded pre-upgrade checkpoint."
msgstr "候选版本能够恢复、处理代表性流量、产生预期副作用并完成新检查点；仍可从记录的升级前检查点回滚。"

msgid ""
"Alpha checkpoints have no cross-release migration promise, and a "
"checkpoint written by the candidate may not be readable by the old "
"version. Restoring an older point may replay external effects."
msgstr "Alpha 检查点不承诺跨版本迁移，候选版本写入的检查点可能无法被旧版本读取。恢复到较早时间点可能重放外部副作用。"

msgid ""
"Follow [Upgrade Klein jobs](upgrading.md); retain the old artifact, "
"dependency lock, configuration, checkpoint prefix, and "
"deduplication/reconciliation procedure."
msgstr "遵循[升级 Klein 作业](upgrading.md)；保留旧构件、依赖锁、配置、检查点前缀以及去重/对账流程。"

msgid "Run a failure rehearsal"
msgstr "执行故障演练"

msgid ""
"Run the following sequence in an environment with production-equivalent "
"Ray settings and isolated external sinks:"
msgstr "在采用生产等效 Ray 设置且外部 Sink 隔离的环境中，按以下顺序执行："

msgid "Start at normal load and wait for at least two completed checkpoints."
msgstr "以正常负载启动，并等待至少两个检查点完成。"

msgid ""
"Kill one transform worker while its output and replay buffers are "
"nonempty."
msgstr "在转换 worker 的输出和重放缓冲区非空时终止它。"

msgid "Kill a stateful worker after it has accumulated representative state."
msgstr "在有状态 worker 积累了代表性状态后终止它。"

msgid "Interrupt a sink between its external write and checkpoint completion."
msgstr "在 Sink 完成外部写入之后、检查点完成之前中断它。"

msgid ""
"Exit the submitting driver and operate the detached job from another "
"client."
msgstr "退出提交 driver，并从另一个客户端操作分离作业。"

msgid ""
"Stop the cluster, recreate it, and resubmit the same graph with "
"`execution.savepoint.path` set to the recorded completed `chk-N` URI."
msgstr "停止并重新创建集群，然后重新提交相同的图，将 `execution.savepoint.path` 设置为已记录的已完成 `chk-N` URI。"

msgid ""
"Verify source position, state contents, watermarks, output duplicates or "
"transactions, and completion of the first post-restore checkpoint."
msgstr "验证数据源位置、状态内容、水位线、输出重复项或事务，以及恢复后首个检查点是否完成。"

msgid ""
"Do not use `ray-klein stop` as a checkpoint operation. It requests "
"cancellation and does not create a named savepoint. Wait for and record "
"an already completed checkpoint before the planned stop."
msgstr ""
"不要将 `ray-klein stop` 当作检查点操作。它会请求取消，且不会创建具名 "
"savepoint。在计划停止前，请等待并记录一个已经完成的检查点。"

msgid "Record the release decision"
msgstr "记录发布决策"

msgid "Keep this evidence with each production release:"
msgstr "每次生产发布都应保留以下证据："

msgid ""
"artifact and worker-image digests, dependency lock, Python/Ray/Klein "
"versions;"
msgstr "构件和 worker 镜像摘要、依赖锁、Python/Ray/Klein 版本；"

msgid ""
"saved logical/resource plan and canonical configuration with secrets "
"removed;"
msgstr "已保存的逻辑/资源计划，以及已移除密钥的规范配置；"

msgid ""
"job name, namespace, source identities, sink destinations, and checkpoint"
" root;"
msgstr "作业名、命名空间、数据源身份、Sink 目标和检查点根目录；"

msgid "SLA targets and peak-load measurements;"
msgstr "SLA 目标和峰值负载测量结果；"

msgid "failure-injection results and accepted duplicate/loss envelope;"
msgstr "故障注入结果和可接受的重复/丢失范围；"

msgid ""
"latest tested restore checkpoint, restore duration, and rollback "
"checkpoint;"
msgstr "最近测试过的恢复检查点、恢复耗时和回滚检查点；"

msgid ""
"owners for application, Ray cluster, storage, connectors, and incident "
"response."
msgstr "应用、Ray 集群、存储、连接器和事件响应的负责人。"

msgid ""
"A deployment is not ready when a required row is merely “accepted risk” "
"with no owner, expiry, detection signal, and recovery action."
msgstr "如果必需项仅被标记为“接受风险”，却没有负责人、到期时间、检测信号和恢复操作，则部署尚未就绪。"
